Name Ideas for the app: SimplifAI, RIP ( Research Intelligence Platform) Medelio (Making Medical Language Human)
Metrics of Success (Important for Demo)Time saved vs reading original abstract, Comprehension score improvement, User satisfaction rating, Repeat usage
Multi-level simplification : Expert / Student / Patient
How to Monetize: 1. Freemium Model (Best Starting Point)
How it works:
Free users:
Limited summaries per day (e.g., 5)
Paid users:
Unlimited usage
Advanced summaries (multi-level, glossary, insights)
Pricing idea:
$5–15/month (students)
$20–40/month (professionals)

👉 Why it works:

Low barrier → fast growth
Easy upgrade path once users see value
🔌 2. API Access (Fastest Revenue Engine)

Even if your main product is a webpage, your real monetization engine can be behind the scenes.

Offer:
API for:
EdTech platforms
Health apps
Research tools
Pricing:
Pay-per-use (e.g., $0.01–$0.05 per abstract)
Volume discounts

👉 This scales way faster than individual subscriptions.

🏢 3. B2B Licensing (High Ticket 💵)

Turn your webpage into a demo funnel for bigger clients.

Sell to:
Universities
Hospitals
Pharma companies
Offer:
Team dashboards
Bulk summarization
Custom models (domain-specific)
Pricing:
$2,000–$50,000/year contracts

👉 One deal here can outperform thousands of users.

📊 4. “Pro Research Tools” Upsell

Add premium features that justify upgrading:

Batch upload (summarize 50+ papers)
Literature review generator
Export to PDF / PowerPoint
Saved research workspace

👉 Charge as:

Subscription tier upgrade
Or pay-per-report ($5–$25)
🎓 5. Student & University Plans

Huge, often overlooked market.

Strategy:
Offer student discount
Campus-wide licenses
Bonus:
Add features like:
Quiz generation
Study notes

👉 Students become long-term users → strong retention

🌍 6. SEO + Content Monetization (Passive Growth)

Turn your webpage into a traffic engine.

Example:
“Simplified version of latest cancer research”
“Top 10 research papers explained simply”
Monetization:
Ads (Google AdSense)
Sponsored content
Affiliate partnerships (courses, tools)

👉 Works best if you target non-expert audiences

🤝 7. Partnerships (Underrated Growth Hack)

Integrate or partner with:

Research platforms
Healthcare portals
Learning platforms

You could even integrate with tools like:

Notion
Zotero

👉 Monetization:

Revenue sharing
Licensing deals
🧾 8. Pay-Per-Use (Simple & Effective)

Instead of subscription:

$1 = 10 summaries
Or $2–5 per advanced report

👉 Good for:

Casual users
Researchers who don’t want subscriptions
🧠 9. Premium “Explain Better” Modes

Charge for smarter outputs:

“Explain like I’m a doctor”
“Explain like I’m a patient”
“Clinical decision summary”

👉 This creates perceived intelligence tiers, which people pay for.

⚠️ What NOT to do early
Don’t rely only on ads → low revenue
Don’t overprice early → kills growth
Don’t build enterprise features before validation
🚀 Recommended Monetization Roadmap
Phase 1 (0–2 months)
Free tool
Limited usage
Collect users + feedback
Phase 2 (2–4 months)
Add subscription
Launch API
Start charging power users
Phase 3 (4–8 months)
B2B outreach
Team plans
Partnerships
🔥 Simple Winning Formula

👉 Free → Hook → Paid → Scale via B2B

💡 Example Positioning (Sales Angle)

Instead of selling “summaries,” sell:

“Save 80% of literature review time”
“Understand research in 30 seconds”
“Bridge the gap between science and decision-making”


Sales punchline:
“Every day, millions of people leave a doctor’s office with more questions than answers. They hear complex terms, complicated diagnoses, and instructions they don’t fully understand. And in healthcare, confusion isn’t just frustrating — it’s dangerous.


Medelio — Making medical language human.

Medelio transforms complex medical jargon into clear, simple, human language — instantly. Whether it’s a diagnosis, a prescription, or a lab result, Medelio empowers patients to truly understand what’s happening in their own bodies.

Because when people understand their health, they make better decisions, follow treatments more accurately, and feel more in control of their lives.
